    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 18 @ 2019/2020",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The SI unit of permittivity is:",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "\\(N^2m^2/C^2\\)",
        "\\(C^2/Nm^2\\)",
        "\\(Nm/C^2\\)",
        "\\(Nm^2/C\\)",
        "None"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\(C^2/Nm^2\\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Permittivity (\\(\\epsilon\\)) appears in Coulomb's law: \\(F = \\frac{1}{4\\pi\\epsilon}\\frac{q_1q_2}{r^2}\\). Solving for units: \\([\\epsilon] = \\frac{C^2}{N\\cdot m^2}\\)."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Permittivity",
      "SI Units",
      "Electricity & Magnetism",
      "Electric Fields",
      "Electrostatics"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 34 @ 2019/2020",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Capacitance of a capacitor depends upon?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "size of plate",
        "distance between plates",
        "nature of dielectric between plate",
        "all of the above"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "all of the above"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Capacitance \\(C\\) is determined by: (1) Plate area \\(A\\) (\\(C \\propto A\\)), (2) Distance between plates \\(d\\) (\\(C \\propto 1/d\\)), and (3) Dielectric material's permittivity \\(\\epsilon\\) (\\(C = \\frac{\\epsilon A}{d}\\))."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Capacitance",
      "Parallel Plate Capacitor",
      "Dielectric",
      "Electrostatics",
      "Permittivity"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 40 @ 2019/2020",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A 4μF capacitor is desired. What plate area is needed for a 5cm air gap?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "0.023×10¹²m²",
        "0.023×10⁶m²",
        "0.023m²",
        "0.023×10¹⁴m²"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "0.023×10⁶m²"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Using \\(C = \\frac{\\epsilon_0 A}{d}\\), solve for \\(A\\): \\(A = \\frac{C \\cdot d}{\\epsilon_0} = \\frac{(4\\times10^{-6}F)(0.05m)}{8.85\\times10^{-12}F/m} \\approx 0.023\\times10^6 m^2\\)."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Capacitance",
      "Parallel Plate Capacitor",
      "Permittivity",
      "Electrostatics",
      "Electricity & Magnetism"
    ]
  },
